{"type":"finding","id":"R2-I1-P2-001","iteration":1,"mode":"review","dimension":"maintainability","severity":"P2","title":"Skill-scope path literals still have multiple source-code representations","claim":"The .opencode/skill scope contract is represented as an exported glob, a private regex, and a SQL LIKE literal, so future changes to the skill scope require coordinated edits across multiple source-code encodings.","evidenceRefs":[".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/code_graph/lib/index-scope-policy.ts:9",".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/utils/index-scope.ts:48-50",".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/utils/index-scope.ts:63-64",".opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/code_graph/lib/code-graph-db.ts:586-592",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/007-code-graph/009-end-user-scope-default/plan.md:127-129"],"counterevidenceSought":"Checked indexer config, walker guard, scan handler, schema/docs, and focused tests; current behavior is consistent for the present .opencode/skill scope and tests cover default/env/per-call precedence.","alternativeExplanation":"Different representations may be intentional because globs, regex path checks, and SQL LIKE predicates require different syntaxes; however, the policy module can still own helper constants/functions that generate or centralize those representations.","finalSeverity":"P2","confidence":0.82,"downgradeTrigger":"Downgrade to ruled_out if maintainers explicitly define the SQL/status count and path regex as separate contracts that are expected to diverge from CODE_GRAPH_SKILL_EXCLUDE_GLOBS."}
